tool_input.messages:
**Jekyll Work Card Layout Fix - Date and Text Always at Bottom**

**Problem**: Recent insights cards had inconsistent layout where date and meta information wasn't consistently positioned at the bottom of cards with varying content heights.

**Solution**: Modified the `.work-card` CSS to use flexbox layout with proper flex properties:

**Key Changes in `_sass/partials/_design-system.scss`**:

1. **Work Card Container** (line ~2391):
```scss
.work-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  height: 100%;
  // other existing styles...
}
```

2. **Work Card Content** (line ~2419):
```scss
.work-card-content {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  height: 100%;
  // other existing styles...
}
```

3. **Description Section** (line ~2444):
```scss
.work-card-description {
  flex-grow: 1;  // Takes up available space
  // other existing styles...
}
```

4. **Meta Section** (line ~2454):
```scss
.work-card-meta {
  margin-top: auto;  // Pushes to bottom
  // other existing styles...
}
```

**HTML Structure** (`_includes/recent-posts.html`):
```html
<article class="work-card work-card--insight">
  <div class="work-card-header"><!-- status --></div>
  <div class="work-card-content">
    <h3 class="work-card-title"><!-- title --></h3>
    <p class="work-card-description"><!-- description --></p>
    <div class="work-card-meta"><!-- date & category --></div>
  </div>
</article>
```

**Result**: Date and category information now consistently appears at the bottom of each card regardless of content length variations.

